<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Fish1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Fish,</orth> subst. 1) an animal that lives in water and breathes by means of gills: <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.1.112" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 1, 112</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.25" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 25</bibl>. 29 etc. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.2.30" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.2.30" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 30</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.266.30" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 266</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 1, 82</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.114" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 114</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.1.26" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 26</bibl> (fem.). <bibl n="shak. aww 3.6.92" default="NO" valid="yes">Alls III, 6, 92</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.279" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 279</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.279" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 279</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.2.91" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.151" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 151</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.3.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 3, 89</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.3.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 3, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.122" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 1, 122</bibl>. Unchanged in the plur.: <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.184" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 184</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.1.23" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 1, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.79" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.1.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 1, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.200" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 200</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.4.91" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 4, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 4.7.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 7, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 36</bibl>. Plur. <cit><quote>--es:</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 1100" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1100</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. err 2.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 1, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.25" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.79" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 2, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 1, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.426" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 426</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.5.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 5, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.153" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 153</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 1, 70</bibl>. <cit><quote>as whole as a f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.5.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 5, 20</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) the flesh of fish, used as food: <bibl n="shak. aww 5.2.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Alls V, 2, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 4, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.86" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 1, 86</bibl>. <cit><quote>'tis well thou art not f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 36</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>at flesh or f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. err 3.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 1, 22</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>neither f. nor flesh,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.3.144" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 3, 144</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>half f., half flesh,</quote> <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 1, 27</bibl></cit>.
